    "type": "message",
    "text": "I play a lot of video games in general and both of these games are in a small niche of games that really try to get you thinking. They also tap into what’s great / native about the medium -- e.g. puzzles as constructivist learning devices\n\nI’ve personally never understood why most games focus on things like story, movies / books IMO are way better at linear story telling (I know some games do nonlinear stuff which is more interesting at least / unique to the games medium!)",
